{{short description|New Zealand cricketer (1930–1985)}}

==Personal life==
Chapple worked as a schoolteacher, and then as a school inspector.<ref>D. J. Cameron, ''Caribbean Crusade: The New Zealand Cricketers in the West Indies 1972'', Hodder & Stoughton, Auckland, 1972, p. 17.</ref> At the time of his death in July 1985 he was the district senior inspector of primary schools in [[Hamilton, New Zealand|Hamilton]].<ref name=MA>Matthew Appleby, ''New Zealand Test Cricket Captains'', Reed Publishing, Auckland, 2002, p. 76.</ref> He and his wife Frances had a daughter and two sons.<ref name=MA/>

